communicated by:
ProMED
<promed@promedmail.org>

[SARS-CoV-2 is an enveloped, positive-sense, and single-stranded RNA virus of around 30 kb and is classified to B coronaviruses. On the other hand, CCHF, caused by a single-strand, enveloped RNA virus belonging to the genus _Orthonairovirus_ in the family Nairoviridae, is a zoonotic viral disease and is transmitted to people through a tick bite. However, transmission via the blood, secretions, organs, or other bodily fluids of infected persons can also be seen.

Fever, malaise, nausea, vomiting, abdominal pain, myalgia, petechia, and ecchymosis are common clinical presentations of CCHF, whereas fever, dry cough, weakness, shortness of breath, and loss of taste or smell are common symptoms of COVID-19. CCHF results in hemorrhage, while COVID-19 can cause thrombosis [https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC7266772/].

Coinfections with the 2 viruses have not been documented or reported before, but CCHF should be considered in differential diagnoses, particularly in COVID-19 cases in endemic regions. - Mod.UBA

